WERETIGER

Weretigers balance the speed of the werewolf with the power of the werebear.
They are excellent hunters and ambush predators, with strong PP for combat
precision and high Spd.  Weretiger packs tend toward smaller territories than
wolves but are no less dangerous.  Some weretigers operate as solitary hunters
across wide ranges.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 3-18   ME: 3-18   MA: 3-18   PS: 12-32 (Supernatural)
  PP: 7-22   PE: 10-30  PB: 5-20   Spd: 8-28

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 3d6 x10 + 40 (approx 70-220 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Rapid regeneration: 2d6 MDC per melee round
  - Enhanced smell
  - Good PP and Spd; precise and fast

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Vulnerable to silver: double damage
  - Lycanthropy risk to victims

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

